  "interpretation": "Image Texture now adapts the Grid UV field from POINT to FACE before nonlinear sampling, the extracted legacy HSV group follows Blender's channel and clamped color-storage semantics, and the authored Greater Than mask is evaluated once per raster sample. The browser then accumulates 64 complete jittered half-float frames with Blender's legacy Eevee Blackman-Harris sequence. The 64-sample pixel correlation rises from 0.1742 to 0.9683 and binary disagreement falls from 0.3028 to 0.0395. The residual is concentrated in cross-renderer raster coverage and antialiasing, so exact shader parity is not claimed."
